troposphere. Now we diagnose the corresponding
thermal budget of the tropical global average
atmospheric temperature variability, finding it
largest in the lower stratosphere (similar to 0.8
degrees K), decreasing downward into the lower
troposphere (similar to 0.15 degrees K) and the
upper ocean (similar to 0.05 degrees K). These
diagnostics find quasi- decadal temperature
variability in the tropical lower stratosphere
arising from a thermal balance between anomalous
radiative forcing (1.0 - 1.5 W m(-2)) by ozone
absorption of the 11-year signal in solar UV
