Atlantic warmth and tropical cyclone activity. In
addition, this analysis indicates that late
twentieth century tropospheric aerosol cooling has
offset a substantial fraction of anthropogenic
warming in the region and has thus likely suppressed
even greater potential increases in tropical cyclone
activity.},
