instrumental period tended to be more severe than
those after 1900. In general, decadal scale dry
events were longer and more severe prior to 1900. In
particular, dry events in the late 13th, 16th, and
18th Centuries surpass the magnitude and duration of
droughts seen in the Uinta Basin after 1900. The
last four decades of the 20th Century also represent
one of the wettest periods in the
reconstruction. The proxy record indicates that the
instrumental record (approximately 1900 to the
Present) underestimates the potential frequency and
severity of severe, sustained droughts in this area,
