probability of any decadal scale drought exceeding
the duration of the 1954 through 1964 drought is 94
percent, while the probability for any wet event
exceeding the duration of the 1965 through 1999 wet
spell is only 1 percent. Hence, estimates of future
water availability in the Uinta Basin and forecasts
for exports to the Colorado River, based on the 1961
to 1990 and 1971 to 2000 "normal" periods, may be
