transient eddy moisture convergence in the SW
compared to GCMs, although both robustly simulate
drying due to enhanced moisture divergence by the
divergent mean flow in a warmer climate. This
enhanced convergence leads to reduced susceptibility
to hydrological change in the RCMs compared to
GCMs.},
