latitudes are associated with increased regional
moisture. We propose that interstadial warming of
the North Atlantic Ocean diverted the westerly storm
track northward, perhaps through weakening of the
Aleutian Low, and thereby reduced moisture delivery
to southwestern North America. A similar response to
future warming would exacerbate aridity in this
already very dry region.},
