East Antarctica. This pattern of meridional flow is
consistent with some projections of circulation
changes arising from anthropogenic climate
change. The precipitation anomaly of the past few
decades in Law Dome is the largest in 750 years, and
lies outside the range of variability for the record
as a whole, suggesting that the drought in Western
Australia may be similarly unusual.},
