descending branch of the zonal Walker
circulation. However, for El Nino events that
co-occur with positive IOD (pIOD) events, Indian
Ocean conditions act to counter El Nino's
drought-inducing subsidence by enhancing moisture
convergence over the Indian subcontinent, with an
average monsoon season resulting. Decadal
modulations of the frequency of independent and
combined El Nino and pIOD events are consistent with
a strengthened El Nino-Indian monsoon relationship
observed at the start of the 20th century and the
apparent recent weakening of the El Nino-Indian
monsoon relationship.},
