extreme wet periods and thirty-five extreme dry
periods in the 1,425-year precipitation
reconstruction and 30 extreme cool periods and 26
extreme warm periods in 2,262-year temperature
reconstruction. In addition, the reconstructions
were integrated to identify intervals when
conditions were extreme in both climatic variables
(cool/dry, cool/wet, warm/dry, warm/wet). Noteworthy
in the reconstructions are the post-1976 warm/wet
period, unprecedented in the 1,425-year record both
in amplitude and duration, anomalous and prolonged
late 20th century warmth, that while never exceeded,
was nearly equaled in magnitude for brief intervals
in the past, and substantial decadal-scale
