   abstract = {In fall 2022 the Task Force organized a two-part workshop on Leveraging Earth System Science and Modeling to Inform Civil Engineering Design focused on three climatic hazards and one region of relevance to engineering practice. Part I of the workshop addressed extreme temperature and intense rainfall, and part II addressed straight-line winds and coastal hazards. This workshop report is based primarily on the outcomes of structured discussion between climate scientists and engineers during the lengthy breakout sessions of those workshops.},
